{
  "texts": [
    "Magnification and demagnification are implicit in the arrival-time surface, as we will see now.",
    "The contour lines in Fig. 6 hint at magnification.",
    "If one looks at this figure from afar (and tries to ignore the heavy saddle-point contours as much as possible) the regions where contour lines are close together look dark, while the regions with widely-spaced contours appear to be bright.",
    "Now, consider a solution of the lens equation (2) and take a differential around it as",
    "If the Hessian ∇∇τ (θ) is large (small), θ will cause us to move off-source quickly (slowly), and meanwhile the contours will be close together (widely spaced)."
  ]
}